text: Miyakitamak () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kozhay-Semyonovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 675 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 19 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki, 5 km from Kozhay-Semyonovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Miyakitamak
